HEADWORD: Cortge
<hw>Cor`t⟦eacute⟧ge"</hw></mhw>
<pr>(k⟦ocir⟧r`t⟦asl⟧zh")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. It.
<ets>corteggio</ets> train, fr. <ets>corte</ets> court. See
<er>Court</er>.]</ety> <def>A train of attendants; a group following and
attending to some important person.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> retinue, suite, entourage.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a procession, especially a funeral procession
following the casket carrying a dead person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cortes</ent>⟦br⟧
